{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:18:10.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 384, "tokens_out": 452, "elapsed_ms": 6422, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild an accessible landing page for a non-profit environmental organization called \"GreenFuture\". Deliver as index.html, styles.css, app.js, and a11y_report.md.\n\nThe page must be fully conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA. Specific requirements:\n- All images have descriptive alt text (not empty, not \"image\")\n- All form inputs have associated <label> with for attribute\n- Heading hierarchy is sequential: h1 → h2 → h3 (never skip levels)\n- All text has minimum color contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against background\n- A \"Skip to main content\" link is the first focusable element\n- All interactive elements (buttons, links, form controls) are keyboard-accessible\n- Use semantic HTML5: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <footer>\n- ARIA labels where semantic elements are insufficient\n\nDeliver a11y_report.md listing every accessibility rule applied and how it was implemented.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:20:06.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1369, "tokens_out": 780, "elapsed_ms": 115082, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"scaffold-files\",\n      \"description\": \"Create the initial project files: index.html, styles.css, app.js, and a11y_report.md. Set up basic HTML5 structure in index.html with doctype, lang attribute, meta tags for charset and viewport, and link to styles.css and app.js. Ensure index.html includes semantic elements: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <footer>.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"build-structure\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement the page structure in index.html with a 'Skip to main content' link as the first focusable element. Add a top navigation menu, hero section with organization name and mission, about section, initiatives section, contact form with properly labeled inputs (using for/id), and footer. Ensure heading hierarchy (h1 \\u2192 h2 \\u2192 h3) is sequential and all images include descriptive alt text.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"style-accessible-ui\",\n      \"description\": \"Style the page in styles.css to ensure all text has a minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 against its background. Use accessible fonts and spacing. Ensure all interactive elements (buttons, links, form controls) are clearly visible and usable with keyboard focus indicators. Apply responsive design for mobile and desktop.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"implement-interactivity\",\n      \"description\": \"Add keyboard accessibility enhancements in app.js, such as focus management for navigation and form validation. Ensure all interactive elements can be operated via keyboard (Tab, Enter, Space). Use ARIA labels where necessary to improve screen reader experience. Do not disrupt default browser accessibility behaviors.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"generate-a11y-report\",\n      \"description\": \"Populate a11y_report.md with a checklist of WCAG 2.1 Level AA requirements. For each rule (e.g., alt text, label association, contrast ratio, heading order, skip link, keyboard access, semantic HTML, ARIA), document how it was implemented in the code with specific file and element references.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
